usage: adv5g_cli [-h] [--version] [--verbose] [--config CONFIG] <command> ...

Adversarial 5G IDS - Professional Security Analysis Tool

positional arguments:
  <command>        Available commands
    detect         Detect threats in 5G PFCP traffic
    attack         Generate adversarial attacks against models
    defend         Evaluate defense mechanisms and model robustness
    analyze        Generate analysis reports and visualizations
    demo           Run interactive demonstrations

optional arguments:
  -h, --help       show this help message and exit
  --version        show program's version number and exit
  --verbose, -v    Enable verbose output
  --config CONFIG  Path to configuration file

Examples:
  adv5g_cli detect --data sample_traffic.csv --model robust
  adv5g_cli attack --method pgd --epsilon 0.3 --target baseline
  adv5g_cli defend --evaluate --attacks --report
  adv5g_cli analyze --generate-report --output security_report.pdf
  adv5g_cli demo --full-pipeline --interactive

For more information about each command, use:
  adv5g_cli <command> --help

usage: adv5g_cli detect [-h] --data DATA [--model {baseline,robust,both}]
                        [--output OUTPUT] [--threshold THRESHOLD] [--detailed]
                        [--batch-size BATCH_SIZE]

Analyze network traffic for potential security threats using trained ML
models.

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --data DATA, -d DATA  Path to input data file (CSV, NPY, or use "sample" for
                        test data)
  --model {baseline,robust,both}, -m {baseline,robust,both}
                        Model to use for detection (default: robust)
  --output OUTPUT, -o OUTPUT
                        Output file for results (JSON format)
  --threshold THRESHOLD
                        Detection threshold for probability scores (default:
                        0.5)
  --detailed            Show detailed analysis for each sample
  --batch-size BATCH_SIZE
                        Batch size for processing (default: 100)

usage: adv5g_cli attack [-h] [--method {fgsm,pgd,enhanced_pgd,noise}]
                        [--target {baseline,robust,both}] [--epsilon EPSILON]
                        [--samples SAMPLES] [--output OUTPUT]
                        [--save-adversarial SAVE_ADVERSARIAL]
                        [--class-target {0,1,2,3,4}] [--steps STEPS]
                        [--constraint-check]

Test model robustness using various adversarial attack methods.

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --method {fgsm,pgd,enhanced_pgd,noise}, -m {fgsm,pgd,enhanced_pgd,noise}
                        Attack method to use (default: enhanced_pgd)
  --target {baseline,robust,both}
                        Target model(s) for attack (default: both)
  --epsilon EPSILON, -e EPSILON
                        Attack strength (perturbation budget)
  --samples SAMPLES, -n SAMPLES
                        Number of samples to attack (default: 100)
  --output OUTPUT, -o OUTPUT
                        Output file for attack results (JSON format)
  --save-adversarial SAVE_ADVERSARIAL
                        Save adversarial examples to file (NPY format)
  --class-target {0,1,2,3,4}
                        Target specific class for attack
  --steps STEPS         Number of attack steps (for iterative methods)
  --constraint-check    Verify PFCP protocol constraint compliance

usage: adv5g_cli defend [-h] [--evaluate] [--compare-models]
                        [--robustness-test] [--noise-levels NOISE_LEVELS]
                        [--samples SAMPLES] [--output OUTPUT]
                        [--detailed-report] [--save-metrics SAVE_METRICS]

Test and analyze the effectiveness of adversarial defenses.

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --evaluate            Run defense evaluation
  --compare-models      Compare baseline vs robust model performance
  --robustness-test     Run comprehensive robustness testing
  --noise-levels NOISE_LEVELS
                        Comma-separated noise levels for testing (default:
                        0.05,0.1,0.2,0.3,0.5)
  --samples SAMPLES, -n SAMPLES
                        Number of samples for evaluation (default: 100)
  --output OUTPUT, -o OUTPUT
                        Output file for results (JSON format)
  --detailed-report     Generate detailed analysis report
  --save-metrics SAVE_METRICS
                        Save detailed metrics to file

usage: adv5g_cli analyze [-h] [--generate-report] [--system-status]
                         [--model-analysis] [--security-assessment]
                         [--output OUTPUT] [--format {json,html,txt,markdown}]
                         [--include-plots] [--detailed]

Create comprehensive security analysis reports and performance visualizations.

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --generate-report     Generate comprehensive security report
  --system-status       Show current system status and capabilities
  --model-analysis      Analyze model performance and characteristics
  --security-assessment
                        Perform security assessment and risk analysis
  --output OUTPUT, -o OUTPUT
                        Output file for report (JSON, HTML, or TXT format)
  --format {json,html,txt,markdown}
                        Report format (default: json)
  --include-plots       Include performance plots in report
  --detailed            Generate detailed analysis with extended metrics

usage: adv5g_cli demo [-h] [--full-pipeline] [--interactive] [--quick]
                      [--attack-demo] [--defense-demo] [--real-time]
                      [--scenario {presentation,technical,business}]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --full-pipeline       Run complete pipeline demonstration
  --interactive         Enable interactive mode with user prompts
  --quick               Run quick demo (reduced samples and iterations)
  --attack-demo         Demonstrate adversarial attack capabilities
  --defense-demo        Demonstrate defense and robustness capabilities
  --real-time           Simulate real-time threat detection
  --scenario {presentation,technical,business}
                        Demo scenario type (default: presentation)
